description.narrative: Government and other partners have increased capacity to deliver routine and supplementary immunization and respond to disease outbreaks, which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. title.narrative: Government and other partners have increased capacity to deliver routine and supplementary immunization and respond to disease outbreaks

description.narrative: UNICEF continues to directly respond to unprecedented measles outbreaks and directly ensured vaccination of 919,160 (452,973 males and 466,187 females) children six months-15 years in 31 counties through IRRM and Measles reactive campaigns; responding to 54% of outbreaks within 72 hours (194% of the 474,300-annual target). 234,969 pregnant women and women of child bearing age received two doses of tetanus (Td2) while 120,436 received Td1 dose. The Pentavalent 1-3 dropout rate was 21% (target of 18%) in areas of direct UNICEF support. The 2019 Effective Vaccine Management assessment showed an increase in the composite country score to 65% (target 60%). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
